  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening URCS COVID-19 preparedness and respone for effective risk mitigation and detection to control the spread of COVID-19 in high risk border districts.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To strengthen the existing URCS COVID-19 preparedness and response structures and mechanisms to implement timely and effective risk mitigation, detection and response measures to control spread of COVID-19 in high risk border districts.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The whole country is at risk of COVID-19 outbreak, but the national taskforce has listed 42 districts along the borders and those along the truck routes as category 1: high risk and they have been prioritized for response interventions.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Conduct risk communication, social mobilization, community engagement and accountability to communities along the border in 3 border districts of Ntungamo, Lamwo and Adjumani
&#x2022;	Conduct screening and risk communication at 3 border entry points (Mirama Hills in Ntungamo; Ngom oromo and Madi opei in Lamwo). 
&#x2022;	Provide PPE for the volunteers and IPC supplies at the 3 POE and the community along these borders including quarantine centers. 
&#x2022;	Provide WASH equipment and supplies. Set up of handwashing points will be supported through provision of tippy taps, soap and hand washing demonstrations by the volunteers.
&#x2022;	Enhance capacity of URCS to be able to prevent, prepare and respond to COVID-19.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">People crossing border points and local communities living near the border points.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Border districts of Busia, Tororo (Malaba), Rakai (Mutukula), Amuru (Elegu), Ntungamo (Mirama Hills), Isingiro (Kikagati), Lamwo, Adjumani, Kasese, Bundibugyo, Ntoroko, Kisoro and Kanungu.</narrative>
  </description>
